<title type="html"><![CDATA[A Person Will Not Be A Muslim Except By...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1442&amp;p=1543#p1543"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">A person will not be a Muslim except by...</span></strong><br /><br />The great scholar ‘Abdurrahman Ibn Hassan Ibn Muhammad Ibn ‘Abd-el-Wahhab, may Allah have mercy on all of them, said:<br /><br /><strong>&quot;A person will not be a Muslim except by...</strong><br /><br /><ul> - stripping himself off completely from major shirk, <br /> - disassociating himself from it (i.e. major shirk) and those who commit it, <br /> - and hating and opposing them to the best of his ability and strength.”</ul><br /><span style="color: #0000FF"><strong>Translated by 'Abdurrahīm Ibn Muhammad Al-Hadhramī.</strong></span><br /><strong>​Published on Salafi-Dawah.com.</strong><br /><em>​[Ad-Durar-us-Sanniyyah 545/11]</em><br /><br />قال الشيخ عبدالرحمن بن حسن رحمه الله<br />المرء لايكون مسلما إلا بالتجرد من الشرك الأكبر،والبراءة منه وممن فعله،وبغضهم ومعاداتهم بحسب الطاقة،والقدرة<br />الدرر ٥٤٥/١١<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.salafi-dawah.com/a-person-will-not-be-a-muslim-except-by.html">http://www.salafi-dawah.com/a-person-wi ... pt-by.html</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Mon Jul 10, 2017 10:34 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
